      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pastry, chill",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the {{unsalted-butter}} into the {{plain-flour}}, first {{sea-salt-fine}} and {{caster-sugar}} until the mixture looks like coarse breadcrumbs. Beat the yolk of the {{eggs}} with the {{water}} and stir into the flour with a knife until the dough just comes together, add another teaspoon of water if it is dry. Form to a flat disc, wrap, and chill for an hour.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Blind bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C fan. Roll the chilled pastry on a floured surface to a 30 cm round, about 3 mm thick. Lift into the 23 cm tin and press into the corners; trim the overhang to 2 cm and tuck under for a double-thickness rim. Prick the base with a fork. Line with baking paper and ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "blind-bake",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp5q86lz0000i0v4jdo0db27"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " with baking beans for 15 minutes; remove the paper and beans and bake another 5 minutes. Brush the warm pastry with the reserved egg white to seal.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Filling, low bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Drop the oven to 160°C fan. Whisk the {{pumpkin}}, {{soft-brown-sugar}}, {{double-cream}}, the beaten three {{eggs}}, {{cinnamon-ground}}, {{ginger-ground}}, {{cloves}} and the second {{sea-salt-fine}} in a bowl until smooth. Pour into the pastry case. Bake on the middle shelf for 50 to 55 minutes; the edges should be set and the centre should still ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "wobble slightly",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp87k7my0000j4v43gwqbmwz"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ". Cool fully in the tin before slicing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
